{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_29","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' 20260311193151-impl-response-001.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Implementation Response (Iteration 1)\n\n## Changes Made\n1. Hardened project ID handling for active-project safety by rejecting path-like values in [`src/shared/domain.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs) before any filesystem lookup or pointer write. This now blocks `.` / `..`, `/`, and `\\` in `ProjectId::new`, which covers both `project select` and `resolve_active_project`; matching unit and CLI regressions were added in [`tests/unit/domain_test.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/domain_test.rs), [`tests/unit/active_project_test.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/active_project_test.rs), and [`tests/cli.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs).\n2. Fixed `config edit` editor precedence in [`src/adapters/fs.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs) so `$EDITOR` is preferred before `$VISUAL`, with a CLI regression test in [`tests/cli.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs) that sets both variables and verifies the `$EDITOR` script wins. Verification passed with `nix develop --command bash -lc 'cargo test'` and `nix develop --command bash -lc 'cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings'`.\n\n## Could Not Address\n- None\n\n## Pending Changes (Pre-Commit)\n- Uncommitted loop 3 review-response fixes are present in the workspace, including the new artifact file and the validated code/test changes above.\n\n---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
